# Deck Card Management (Deck Editor)

When the user asks to add, remove, or move cards in **"the deck"**, **"the open deck"**, **"the loaded deck"**, **"my deck"**, or any similar phrasing that refers to a deck they have open in the deck editor, the agent must use the appropriate MCP tool so the deck editor UI updates via SSE.

**Do not** only suggest code, curl commands, or manual steps — actually invoke the tool (when the agent has MCP access).

**Prerequisite:** The deck editor server must be running (e.g. `python deck_editor.py` or `main.bat deck-editor`). If a tool returns an error that the editor is unreachable, tell the user to start the deck editor first.

---

## Adding cards: `append_cards_to_deck`

- **`card_names`** (required) — comma-separated card names (e.g. `"Sol Ring"` or `"Lightning Bolt, Counterspell"`).
- **`board`** (optional, default `"main"`) — which board to add to: `"main"`, `"maybe"`, or `"sideboard"`.

### Examples

- "Add Soul Warden to the deck" → `append_cards_to_deck(card_names="Soul Warden")`
- "Add Sol Ring to the sideboard" → `append_cards_to_deck(card_names="Sol Ring", board="sideboard")`
- "Put Lightning Bolt in the maybe board" → `append_cards_to_deck(card_names="Lightning Bolt", board="maybe")`

---

## Removing cards: `remove_cards_from_deck`

- **`card_names`** (required) — comma-separated card names to remove.
- **`board`** (optional, default `"main"`) — which board to remove from: `"main"`, `"maybe"`, or `"sideboard"`.
- **`count`** (optional, default `1`) — how many copies to remove per card name.

### Examples

- "Remove Lightning Bolt from the deck" → `remove_cards_from_deck(card_names="Lightning Bolt")`
- "Remove 2 copies of Sol Ring" → `remove_cards_from_deck(card_names="Sol Ring", count=2)`
- "Remove Counterspell from the sideboard" → `remove_cards_from_deck(card_names="Counterspell", board="sideboard")`

---

## Moving cards: `move_cards_in_deck`

- **`card_names`** (required) — comma-separated card names to move.
- **`from_board`** (required) — source board: `"main"`, `"maybe"`, or `"sideboard"`.
- **`to_board`** (required) — destination board: `"main"`, `"maybe"`, or `"sideboard"`.
- **`count`** (optional, default `1`) — how many copies to move per card name.

### Examples

- "Move Sol Ring to the sideboard" → `move_cards_in_deck(card_names="Sol Ring", from_board="main", to_board="sideboard")`
- "Move Lightning Bolt from the maybe board to the main deck" → `move_cards_in_deck(card_names="Lightning Bolt", from_board="maybe", to_board="main")`
